pageContext.claim: “You look at apples. Japan, foreign tariff -- 17 percent. The United States -- nothing. We get nothing; they get 17. The same apple.”
pageContext.analysis: Japan does have a 17 percent tariff on American apples. But that tariff along with other agricultural tariff would have been phased out had Trump moved forward with the Trans-Pacific Partnership agreement, which he scrapped early in his term.
